Introduction to the task. Gathering material from ethnographic sources and analysing it; designing the unique jewellery or set; choosing suitable materials and techniques; preparing the work plan; making and assembling the jewellery parts; analysing the convenience of wearing the piece; finishing the piece, documenting and presenting it.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Using combined techniqus to design and make unique jewellery or a set.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After successfully completing the course the student is able to make unique jewellery or a set; knows how to gather materials for creating the jewellery, design the jewellery, choose suitable materials and technologies, prepare work process schedule and plan, make the parts of the jewellery and assemble them, finish the jewellery and present it.
